TEI Texts
Created following the guidelines of the Text Encoding Initiative, available in a variety of formats to read, download or link to.
Corpora
Collections of language data comprising a number of texts from different sources, usually compiled for the purposes of linguistic research
Legacy formats
A variety of resources which have been collected since the OTA came into existence in 1976. Some have restricted access, which means that you have to ask for permission to use them, and many are in formats which some users may find difficult to use, although most are plain text. The OTA cannot offer support for dealing with legacy formats.
